===Etymology===
Originally short for “rifled gun”, referring to the spiral grooves inside the barrel. From {{der|en|enm|-}}, from {{der|en|fro|rifler|t=to scrape off, plunder}}, from {{der|en|odt|*riffilōn}} (compare archaic {{cog|nl|rijfelen|t=to scrape}}, {{cog|ang|geriflian|t=to wrinkle}}), frequentative of {{der|en|gem-pro|*rīfaną}} (compare {{cog|non|rífa|t=to tear, break}}). More at {{m|en|rive}}.

